{
  "stem": "8784.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I attended not a formal kind of a school, but I had opportunity to attend some classes-- a religious school more so than anything else.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had a chance to do that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there were no schools, no public schools as we knew them before.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And as we stayed in the ghetto, the situation got worse every day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, and the reason for that was that the Germans would come into the ghetto and occasionally round up 100 people, 500 people and take them into trucks and take them outside of the ghetto to work someplace for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And these work squadrons that they picked up in the ghetto would sometimes go out to shovel snow in the city of Cracow, dig ditches.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in those days, they were preparing for the air raids all the time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So the Jews would be digging trenches on the outside of the ghetto in the area of the parks and so on, unloading carloads of merchandise for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In many situations, those Jews were returned to the ghetto after a day's work.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But on many occasions, some of the Jews did not return to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In other words, whatever happened to them on the outside we don't know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Some people simply disappeared, were killed on the outside of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So this began to instill fear into the population of the ghetto that if you get taken out from the ghetto, you don't know what's going to happen to us, whether we will ever return.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In many situations they rounded up people to, to, in, in what the Germans called Aktions.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
